# ğŸŒ± LifeTracker â€“ Wellness, Habits & Daily Well-Being App

**LifeTracker** is a wellness-focused mobile application designed to help users build healthier daily routines, track habits, monitor mood changes, and maintain overall well-being.  
Developed in **Android Studio using Kotlin**, the app focuses on simplicity, mindfulness, and smooth user experience, aligning with the learning outcomes of the Mobile Application Development module.

---

## âœ¨ Key Features

### ğŸ“Œ 1. Habit Tracker
- Users can add their daily tasks and habits at the start of the day  
- Each habit can be marked as **Pending** or **Completed**  
- Users can visually track daily progress through simple UI indicators  
- Encourages consistency and self-discipline

---

### ğŸ˜Š 2. Mood Tracking
- Users can log their mood throughout the day  
- Each mood entry is associated with expressive **emoji icons**  
- Displays mood patterns with time stamps  
- Helps users understand emotional cycles throughout the day  
- Useful for self-awareness and emotional well-being

---

### ğŸ’§ 3. Hydration Monitoring
- Users can input their daily hydration levels  
- App allows selection of different beverage types  
- Automatically updates a **progress circle** based on fluid intake  
- Shows hydration status using emojis (good/poor level indicators)  
- Encourages maintaining proper health

---

### â° 4. Reminders & Notifications
- Users can set customizable reminders (e.g., *"Stay hydrated!"*)  
- Sends timely notifications  
- Helps busy users practice self-care consistently

